<p:synopses>
<p:synopsis length="short">Half a degree doesn't seem like much but in climate change, it makes all the difference</p:synopsis>
<p:synopsis length="medium">Half a degree doesn't seem like much but in climate change, it makes all the difference.</p:synopsis>
<p:synopsis length="long">One of the stated goals recent United Nations report on climate change is to prevent the planet from warming more than one and a half degrees Celsius. We ask what would happen if the world warmed by, say, two degrees. &#13;
&#13;
Also: Calculating the cost of climate change is doable but difficult -- too difficult says the US Department of Defense; we fact check President Donald Trump on one of his recent statements about climate change; plus we take a journey to the remote Alaskan village of Shishmaref, where climate change and rising sea levels are a present threat.</p:synopsis>
</p:synopses>
